# .aidocs/project-init.aidocs - /project Contract

## Read Order (always)
1) `AIDOCS.md`
2) `.aidocs/index.aidocs`
3) linked shared docs

## Pre-edit checks
- Resolve project root.
- If no git repo: init + initial commit.
- Ensure remote exists. If missing, try `gh repo create <name> --private --source . --remote origin --push`.
- If remote creation fails (no gh/auth/error), STOP and ask for remote/repo target.
- Verify upstream tracking; STOP on failure.

## Analysis
- Discover project docs/router + relevant README/spec docs.
- Analyze build/runtime/db artifacts (read-only DB interrogation proposals only).
- Output Option A (docs->code) and Option B (code->docs) with recommendation.

## Memory bootstrap (template-first)
- Create `/.MEMORY/` from root templates at `.aidocs/templates/memory/**` (copy missing files/directories).
- Required files after bootstrap:
  - `/.MEMORY/NOW.md`
  - `/.MEMORY/rules/standards.md`
  - `/.MEMORY/rules/security.md`
  - `/.MEMORY/system/architecture.md`
  - `/.MEMORY/system/caveats.md`
  - `/.MEMORY/system/decisions.md`
  - `/.MEMORY/daily/YYYY-MM-DD.md`
  - `/.MEMORY/daily/archive/`

## First-init extraction
- Sources (order): root shared docs -> project entry files -> project docs/router -> relevant README/spec docs.
- Merge/edit durable signal into categorized memory files (no duplicate append-only entries).

## Routing update
- Ensure project `AGENTS.md`/`CLAUDE.md` route to `/.MEMORY/*` as canonical operational memory.
- Keep entry files short.

## Archive behavior
- `/archive` promotes from `/.MEMORY/daily/*` into categorized files with merge semantics.
- Processed logs move to `/.MEMORY/daily/archive/`.
